OL,3,CWhy an ancient Greek-style temple was
OL,4,Cbuilt on a hill near Sunderland
OL,6,FSitting atop a hill near Sunderland
OL,7,Fthere stands an unlikely monument in
OL,8,Fthe style of a Greek temple.
OL,10,FPenshaw Monument has been a popular
OL,11,Fspot for visitors for generations.
OL,13,FNow considered an icon of the region,
OL,14,Fit even features on the badge of
OL,16,FThe monument on Penshaw Hill, between
OL,17,FWashington and Houghton-le-Spring, was
OL,18,Fbuilt as a memorial to John George
OL,19,FLambton, the 1st Earl of Durham and a
OL,20,Fcoal mine owner in the area.
