OL,6,FHe added: "Everybody refers to it as
OL,7,Fseeing they're coming back home. It's
OL,8,Fsuch a large significant solid
OL,9,Ffeature. And even the blackness on it
OL,10,Freflects its coal-mining history. It's
OL,11,Fnever been cleaned up."
OL,13,FBut the area is also steeped in the
OL,14,Flegend of the Lambton Worm - a dragon-
OL,15,Flike monster that was said to
OL,16,Fterrorise local villages.
