OL,6,FRob Kilburn, author of Tyne and Weird,
OL,7,Fsaid: "For most people, Penshaw
OL,8,FMonument is associated with the
OL,9,FLambton Worm, which is quite an old
OL,10,Ftale.
OL,12,F"It dates back to the Lambton family
OL,13,Fwho were gentry in the area, connected
OL,14,Fto the River Wear, where there was a
OL,15,Fworm that grew to be more like a
OL,16,Fdragon.
